            <fr:title text="descent data of presheaves">descent data of presheaves</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Given a category <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex>, a <fr:link href="/forest/algm-001B/" title="sieve" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/algm-001B/" display-uri="algm-001B" type="local">sieve</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> and a presheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P : \mathcal {C}^\textrm {op} \to  \mathsf {Set}]]></fr:tex>, a set of <html:strong>descent data</html:strong> or a <html:strong>compatible family</html:strong> is a morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S \to  P]]></fr:tex>. Expanding this, it is a family of <html:em>local sections</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s \in  \Gamma (U, P)]]></fr:tex> assigned for each morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \to  A]]></fr:tex> in the sieve <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, such that the local sections are compatible on restriction. There is an obvious map from the sections <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma (A, P)]]></fr:tex> to the descent data given by restriction.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
  More generally, given a general <fr:link href="/forest/algm-0019/" title="coverage" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/algm-0019/" display-uri="algm-0019" type="local">cover</fr:link>, a set of descent data is a family of sections <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_i \in  \Gamma (U_i, P)]]></fr:tex> for each morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_i : U_i \to  A]]></fr:tex> in the cover, such that in any common restriction of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U_i]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U_j]]></fr:tex>, the sections agree. This can be equivalently expressed as the descent data of the sieve generated by the cover.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
